# tstack Project Context

**What it is:** Claude Code plugin — structured dev workflow with commands, agents, skills. Three tiers: Task (minutes), Feature (hours), Mission (days/weeks).

## Key Paths (go here first)

| What | Where |
|------|-------|
| Plugin manifest | `.claude-plugin/plugin.json` |
| Slash commands | `commands/<category>/*.md` (git/, lifecycle/, planning/, quality/, testing/, general/, utility/) |
| Agents | `agents/core/*.md`, `agents/lifecycle/*.md` |
| Skills | `skills/<name>/SKILL.md` |
| Hooks | `hooks/hooks.json`, `hooks/*.js` |
| Full docs | `CLAUDE.md` — read for conventions, state system, agent protocol |

## Adding Components

- **Command:** Drop `commands/<category>/<name>.md` with YAML frontmatter (`name`, `description`, `argument-hint`, `model`)
- **Agent:** Drop `agents/<category>/<name>.md` with frontmatter (`name`, `description`, `model`, `tools`, `domain`, `maxTurns`)
- **Skill:** Create `skills/<name>/SKILL.md` with frontmatter (`name`, `description`, `user-invocable`)

## State System (`.tstack/`)

Agents read/write here. On feature work: read `STATE.md`, `DECISIONS.md`, `features/<n>/plan.md` before implementing.

## Quality Pipeline

`pnpm lint → pnpm build → pnpm test` — stop on first failure. Never commit broken code.
